      • calculate

        public java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Double> calculate(long start,
                                                                          long end,
                                                                          long step,
                                                                          java.lang.String datum)
        calculate tides (heights) for an interval with a single nodal correction
        Parameters:
        start - start time of the interval for which to calculate the heights in seconds since the java epochStart (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        end - end time of the interval for which to calculate the heights in seconds since the java epochStart (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        step - step size in seconds for which to calculate the heights
        datum - datum to add to all values (can be null)
        Returns:
        hashmap of time, height pairs

      • calculateExtremes

        public java.util.List<Extreme> calculateExtremes(long start,
                                                 long end,
                                                 java.lang.String datum)
        Calculates all extremes (high and low tides) in the interval time...time+intervalInMillis. The nodal corrections are only calculated once to speed up calculations.
        Parameters:
        start - start time of the interval for which to calculate the extremes in seconds since the java epochStart (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        end - end time of the interval for which to calculate the extremes in seconds since the java epochStart (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        datum - datum to add to all values (can be null)
        Returns:
        extremes in the specified interval as Extreme objects
